  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>steaks</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature and boil a kettle</p><p>Grate the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on), then add to the middle of a tea towel and bring the four corners together to form a ball, twist the ball and squeeze out as much of the liquid as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>grated potato</strong> to a bowl and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> to a cold, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), then add 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> piles of <strong>grated potato</strong> to the pan and firmly shape them into potato cakes – these are your<strong> potato röstis</strong></p><p>Heat the pan over a medium-high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until golden, then flip the rösti carefully with a spatula and cook for 4-5 min further or until golden brown</p><p>Tip: Don't move the rösti around the pan too much so they stay together!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped parsnip</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat and cook for 15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked parsnip</strong> and add it to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>clotted cream</strong> and 75ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [125ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> parsnip purée</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the röstis are golden, transfer them to a baking tray and reserve the pan</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until golden and cooked through</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> soy sauce</strong> and <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>redcurrant stock</strong></p><p>Pat the <strong>sirloin steaks </strong>dry with kitchen paper, drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat and once very hot, add the <strong>seasoned steaks</strong></p><p>For <strong>rare</strong>, cook for 2-3 min max on each side</p><p>For <strong>medium-rare</strong>, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>For <strong>medium</strong>, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Once the steaks are cooked, transfer them to a plate to rest</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the steaks are resting, reduce the heat to medium and add the<strong> redcurrant stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened so it coats the back of a wooden spoon</p><p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and give it a good mix up until melted – this is your <strong>redcurrant jus</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>parsnip purée</strong> to a pot over a low heat and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and add it to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to wilt – this is your <strong>garlic spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1852.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
